main event: A circular, willow-shaped object was observed by an Air Force officer at an altitude of 17,000 feet, estimated to be at 45-50,000 feet.
interesting points: The object was initially thought to be a balloon, but it seemed to be going against the wind.
Motion picture film was taken of the object, but it was poor quality and showed no distinguishable features.
The case was concluded as 'Was Balloon, Probably Balloon, Possibly Balloon'.
Insufficient data was available for a proper evaluation of the sighting.
